The paper discusses techniques and countermeasures related to cybercrime, specifically domain name typosquatting. This falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) as well as information retrieval (cs.IR) since the paper discusses methods for generating typosquatted domain names. The paper also touches on social implications (cs.SI) and cybercrime (cs.CY) which are related sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses potential technical countermeasures (cs.SE) which could be used to prevent domain name typosquatting.
